Description: Public Facilities Group (PFG) is a leading practitioner of Public-Private Partnerships (P3) for Social Infrastructure.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Public Facilities Group (PFG) is a leading practitioner of Public-Private Partnerships (P3) for Social Infrastructure.  Their professional staff have completed 28 projects with a total development cost of $1.8 billion.   Each of these projects have been completed on or ahead of schedule and on or under budget with a lower cost than their public partners had experienced with alternative delivery models.  They advocate the use of the New American Approach of P3 delivery for Social Infrastructure.  This approach blends tax-exempt financing with private development, operations and maintenance, to maximize public benefit and minimize public cost.  The New American Approach offers private guarantees of both cost and schedule and builds in safeguards that allow the public to secure ultimate project control whenever they desire to do so.    Their team has significant experience in real estate development and finance.  In Public-Private Partnerships they assist the public in structuring P3 delivery and they serve as the obligated party, using 63-20 and 501(c)(3) bonds to finance and own public facilities for the public benefit. Their experience is diverse. They have worked with public universities developing student housing, dining halls, and research facilities, with cities constructing city halls and parking garages and with counties and state governments delivering administrative buildings, medical office building and justice centers.    They are proud of their track record in helping public agencies find cost-effective and efficient solutions to their own operational needs as well as those of their constituents.

In addition to our work with UN NGO’s and renewable energy companies, we have also had the privilege of working with a wide range of other clients across a variety of industries. Our expertise in software design and engineering, combined with our commitment to delivering high-quality products and services, has earned us a reputation as a trusted partner for businesses and organizations looking to succeed in the digital age.

The process of connecting to your common circle on a new social network requires that you authenticate one or more of your existing networks and select which profiles you want to friend or follow. Konfect will simplify that process. And when that's done Konfect wants to be your go-to source for managing your connections across social networks. With Konfect you will never have to start from blank when you join a new social network. The intelligence in Konfect will benefit you in many ways beyond connections to the right people across networks.
